('容光煥發的、喜悅的', 'Radiant', '/ˈreɪdiənt/', 'The bride looked absolutely radiant on her wedding day.', '新娘在婚禮當天容光煥發。', '5', 19),
('深思的、反思的', 'Reflective', '/rɪˈflektɪv/', 'He was in a reflective mood after the conversation.', '對話後他陷入深思。', '5', 19),
('不情願的、勉強的', 'Reluctant', '/rɪˈlʌktənt/', 'She was reluctant to share her personal story.', '她不情願分享自己的個人故事。', '5', 19),
('憤恨的、怨恨的', 'Resentful', '/rɪˈzentfəl/', 'He felt resentful about being passed over for promotion.', '錯失升職機會讓他感到憤恨。', '5', 19),
('不安的、焦躁的', 'Restless', '/ˈrestləs/', 'I feel restless when I have nothing to do.', '無事可做時我感到焦躁不安。', '5', 19),
('寧靜的、安詳的', 'Serene', '/səˈriːn/', 'The lake looked perfectly serene in the morning light.', '湖水在晨光中顯得非常寧靜。', '5', 19),
('懷疑的、多疑的', 'Skeptical', '/ˈskeptɪkəl/', 'She was skeptical about the new treatment''s effectiveness.', '她對新療法的效果持懷疑態度。', '5', 19),
('堅忍的、不動聲色的', 'Stoic', '/ˈstoʊɪk/', 'He remained stoic despite the tragedy.', '儘管遭遇悲劇，他仍然堅忍不拔。', '5', 19),
('非常興奮的、激動的', 'Thrilled', '/θrɪld/', 'The children were thrilled to visit the amusement park.', '孩子們對去遊樂園感到非常興奮。', '5', 19),
('寧靜的、安靜的', 'Tranquil', '/ˈtræŋkwɪl/', 'The garden provides a tranquil escape from city life.', '花園提供了遠離城市生活的寧靜空間。', '5', 19),
('不安的、不自在的', 'Uneasy', '/ʌnˈiːzi/', 'I felt uneasy about the stranger following me.', '陌生人跟蹤讓我感到不安。', '5', 19),
('樂觀的、積極的', 'Upbeat', '/ˈʌpbiːt/', 'His upbeat personality lifts everyone''s spirits.', '他樂觀的個性提振了每個人的精神。', '5', 19),
('脆弱的、易受傷的', 'Vulnerable', '/ˈvʌlnərəbəl/', 'Opening up made her feel vulnerable but authentic.', '敞開心扉讓她感到脆弱但真實。', '5', 19),
('異想天開的、古怪的', 'Whimsical', '/ˈwɪmzɪkəl/', 'Her whimsical sense of humor brightened everyone''s day.', '她異想天開的幽默感照亮了每個人的一天。', '5', 19),
('惆悵的、思念的', 'Wistful', '/ˈwɪstfəl/', 'She had a wistful look when talking about her childhood.', '談到童年時她露出惆悵的神色。', '5', 19),
('擔心的、憂慮的', 'Worried', '/ˈwʌrid/', 'Parents are naturally worried about their children''s safety.', '父母天性會擔心孩子的安全。', '5', 19),
('被收養的孩子', 'Adopted child', '/əˈdɑːptɪd tʃaɪld/', 'Their adopted child brings immense joy to the family.', '他們的養子為家庭帶來巨大的快樂。', '3', 20),
('收養家庭', 'Adoptive family', '/əˈdɑːptɪv ˈfæməli/', 'Adoptive families go through extensive screening processes.', '收養家庭需要經過廣泛的審查程序。', '3', 20),
('養父母', 'Adoptive parent', '/əˈdɑːptɪv ˈperənt/', 'Adoptive parents provide loving homes for children in need.', '養父母為有需要的孩子提供充滿愛的家庭。', '3', 20),
('祖先', 'Ancestor', '/ˈænsestər/', 'Many families maintain traditions passed down from their ancestors.', '許多家庭維持著從祖先傳下來的傳統。', '3', 20),
('姑姑/阿姨', 'Aunt', '/ænt/', 'My aunt has always been like a second mother to me.', '我的姑姑對我來說一直像第二個母親。', '3', 20),
('權威主義的', 'Authoritarian', '/əˌθɔːrəˈteriən/', 'Authoritarian parents tend to have strict rules and high expectations.', '權威主義的父母往往有嚴格的規則和高期望。', '3', 20),
('重組家庭', 'Blended family', '/ˈblendɪd ˈfæməli/', 'Blended families require patience and understanding to create harmonious relationships.', '重組家庭需要耐心和理解來創造和諧的關係。', '3', 20),
('養家糊口的人', 'Breadwinner', '/ˈbredˌwɪnər/', 'In modern families, both parents often serve as breadwinners.', '在現代家庭中，父母雙方通常都是養家糊口的人。', '3', 20),
('破碎家庭', 'Broken home', '/ˈbroʊkən hoʊm/', 'Children from broken homes may face emotional challenges.', '來自破碎家庭的孩子可能面臨情感挑戰。', '3', 20),
('兄弟', 'Brother', '/ˈbrʌðər/', 'My brother and I share many common interests.', '我的兄弟和我有許多共同興趣。', '3', 20),
('姊夫/妹夫/配偶的兄弟', 'Brother-in-law', '/ˈbrʌðər ɪn lɔː/', 'My brother-in-law works in the same industry as I do.', '我的姊夫和我在同一個行業工作。', '3', 20),
('照護者', 'Caregiver', '/ˈkerˌɡɪvər/', 'Caregivers play essential roles in supporting elderly family members.', '照護者在支持年長家庭成員方面扮演重要角色。', '3', 20),
('育兒', 'Child-rearing', '/tʃaɪld ˈrɪrɪŋ/', 'Modern child-rearing practices emphasize emotional intelligence.', '現代育兒實踐強調情緒智能。', '3', 20),
('無子女夫妻', 'Childless couple', '/ˈtʃaɪldləs ˈkʌpəl/', 'The number of childless couples is increasing in developed countries.', '已開發國家中無子女夫妻的數量正在增加。', '3', 20),
('關係緊密的', 'Close-knit', '/kloʊs nɪt/', 'We''re a close-knit family who supports each other through thick and thin.', '我們是一個關係緊密的家庭，彼此患難與共。', '3', 20),
('成年、成人禮', 'Coming of age', '/ˈkʌmɪŋ əv eɪdʒ/', 'Coming of age ceremonies mark the transition to adulthood.', '成人禮標誌著向成年期的過渡。', '3', 20),
('表兄弟姊妹/堂兄弟姊妹', 'Cousin', '/ˈkʌzən/', 'My cousins and I grew up together like siblings.', '我的表兄弟姊妹和我一起長大，就像兄弟姊妹一樣。', '3', 20),
('女兒', 'Daughter', '/ˈdɔːtər/', 'Their daughter just graduated from medical school.', '他們的女兒剛從醫學院畢業。', '3', 20),
('媳婦', 'Daughter-in-law', '/ˈdɔːtər ɪn lɔː/', 'The daughter-in-law fits perfectly into our family.&nbsp;', '這位媳婦完美地融入了我們的家庭。', '3', 20),
('後裔', 'Descendant', '/dɪˈsendənt/', 'She is a direct descendant of a famous poet.', '她是一位著名詩人的直系後裔。', '3', 20),
('功能失調的', 'Dysfunctional', '/dɪsˈfʌŋkʃənəl/', 'Children from dysfunctional families may require additional psychological support.', '來自功能失調家庭的兒童可能需要額外的心理支持。', '3', 20),
('空巢症候群', 'Empty nest syndrome', '/ˈempti nest ˈsɪndroʊm/', 'Many parents experience empty nest syndrome when children leave home.', '許多父母在孩子離家時會經歷空巢症候群。', '3', 20),
('疏遠的、關係惡化的', 'Estranged', '/ɪˈstreɪndʒd/', 'Unfortunately, he became estranged from his siblings after the inheritance dispute.&nbsp;', '不幸的是，在遺產糾紛後，他與兄弟姊妹疏遠了。', '3', 20),
('大家庭、擴展家庭', 'Extended family', '/ɪkˈstendɪd ˈfæməli/', 'In many cultures, extended family members play crucial roles in child-rearing.', '在許多文化中，大家庭成員在育兒方面扮演重要角色。', '3', 20),
('家庭出遊', 'Family outing', '/ˈfæməli ˈaʊtɪŋ/', 'Regular family outings strengthen relationships and create memories.', '定期家庭出遊加強關係並創造回憶。', '3', 20),
('家庭聚會', 'Family reunion', '/ˈfæməli riˈjuːnjən/', 'Annual family reunions help maintain strong family bonds.', '年度家庭聚會有助於維持牢固的家庭關係。', '3', 20),
('父親', 'Father', '/ˈfɑːðər/', 'My father has been teaching mathematics for over twenty years.', '我的父親教數學超過二十年了。', '3', 20),
('岳父/公公', 'Father-in-law', '/ˈfɑːðər ɪn lɔː/', 'My father-in-law and I enjoy fishing together.', '我的岳父和我喜歡一起釣魚。', '3', 20),
('寄養兒童', 'Foster child', '/ˈfɔːstər tʃaɪld/', 'The foster child adapted well to the new environment.', '寄養兒童很好地適應了新環境。', '3', 20),
('寄養家庭', 'Foster family', '/ˈfɔːstər ˈfæməli/', 'Foster families provide temporary care for children in need.', '寄養家庭為有需要的兒童提供臨時照護。', '3', 20),
('寄養父母', 'Foster parent', '/ˈfɔːstər ˈperənt/', 'Foster parents require special training and certification.', '寄養父母需要特殊訓練和認證。', '3', 20),
('孫子/孫女', 'Grandchild', '/ˈɡrændˌtʃaɪld/', 'Their grandchildren visit every weekend.', '他們的孫子女每個週末都會來拜訪。', '3', 20),
('祖父母/外祖父母', 'Grandparent', '/ˈɡrændˌperənt/', 'My grandparents raised me with traditional values.&nbsp;', '我的祖父母用傳統價值觀養育我。', '3', 20),
('曾孫', 'Great-grandchild', '/ɡreɪt ˈɡrændˌtʃaɪld/', 'She lived to see her great-grandchildren grow up.&nbsp;', '她活著看到她的曾孫長大。', '3', 20),
('曾祖父母', 'Great-grandparent', '/ɡreɪt ˈɡrændˌperənt/', 'I was fortunate to know my great-grandparents personally.&nbsp;', '我很幸運能親自認識我的曾祖父母。', '3', 20),
('監護人', 'Guardian', '/ˈɡɑːrdiən/', 'The court appointed her aunt as the child''s legal guardian.', '法院指定她的阿姨為孩子的法定監護人。', '3', 20),
('同父異母/同母異父兄弟', 'Half-brother', '/hæf ˈbrʌðər/', 'My half-brother lives with his mother most of the time.&nbsp;', '我的同父異母兄弟大部分時間和他母親住在一起。', '3', 20),
('同父異母/同母異父姊妹', 'Half-sister', '/hæf ˈsɪstər/', 'Despite being half-sisters, we share a strong bond.', '儘管是同父異母姊妹，我們有很強的情感聯繫。', '3', 20),
('和諧的', 'Harmonious', '/hɑːrˈmoʊniəs/', 'They maintain a harmonious relationship despite their different personalities.', '儘管性格不同，他們仍保持和諧的關係。', '3', 20),
('繼承人', 'Heir', '/er/', 'The eldest son is traditionally the heir to the family business.', '長子傳統上是家族企業的繼承人。', '3', 20),
('傳承、遺產', 'Heritage', '/ˈherɪtɪdʒ/', 'Preserving family heritage is important for future generations.', '保存家庭傳承對後代很重要。', '3', 20),
('丈夫', 'Husband', '/ˈhʌzbənd/', 'Her husband supports her career ambitions completely.', '她的丈夫完全支持她的職業理想。', '3', 20),
('直系親屬', 'Immediate family', '/ɪˈmiːdiət ˈfæməli/', 'My immediate family consists of my parents, my younger sister, and myself.', '我的直系親屬包括我的父母、妹妹和我自己。', '3', 20),
('姻親', 'In-laws', '/ˈɪn lɔːz/', 'Building good relationships with in-laws can strengthen family bonds.', '與姻親建立良好關係能加強家庭聯繫。', '3', 20),
('大家庭', 'Large family', '/lɑːrdʒ ˈfæməli/', 'Managing a large family requires excellent organizational skills.', '管理大家庭需要出色的組織能力。', '3', 20),
('遺產、傳承', 'Legacy', '/ˈleɡəsi/', 'Long-term impact: "Parents hope to leave a positive legacy for their children."', '父母希望為孩子留下正面的傳承。', '3', 20),
('母權家庭', 'Matriarchal family', '/ˌmeɪtriˈɑːrkəl ˈfæməli/', 'Some cultures feature matriarchal families where women hold authority.', '某些文化以母權家庭為特色，女性擁有權威。', '3', 20),
('母親', 'Mother', '/ˈmʌðər/', 'My mother works as a nurse in the local hospital.', '我的母親在當地醫院擔任護士。', '3', 20),
('岳母/婆婆', 'Mother-in-law', '/ˈmʌðər ɪn lɔː/', 'My mother-in-law gives excellent cooking advice.', '我的岳母給予很好的烹飪建議。', '3', 20),
('多代同堂家庭', 'Multi-generational household', '/ˈmʌlti ˌdʒenəˈreɪʃənəl ˈhaʊshoʊld/', 'Multi-generational households are common in many Asian cultures.', '多代同堂家庭在許多亞洲文化中很常見。', '3', 20),
('疏忽的', 'Neglectful', '/nɪˈɡlektfəl/', 'Neglectful parenting can lead to behavioral issues in children.', '疏忽的教養可能導致孩子出現行為問題。', '3', 20),
('侄子/外甥', 'Nephew', '/ˈnefju/', 'My nephew is extremely talented in music.', '我的侄子在音樂方面非常有天賦。', '3', 20),
('最近親屬', 'Next of kin', '/nekst əv kɪn/', 'Please provide your next of kin for emergency contact purposes.', '請提供您的最近親屬作為緊急聯絡人。', '3', 20),
('侄女/外甥女', 'Niece', '/niːs/', 'My niece just won a scholarship to university.', '我的侄女剛獲得大學獎學金。', '3', 20),
('核心家庭', 'Nuclear family', '/ˈnuːkliər ˈfæməli/', 'The traditional nuclear family model is evolving in response to changing social dynamics.', '傳統的核心家庭模式正因應變化的社會動態而演進。', '3', 20),
('養育的、關愛的', 'Nurturing', '/ˈnɜːrtʃərɪŋ/', 'A nurturing environment helps children develop confidence.', '養育性的環境幫助孩子培養自信心。', '3', 20),
('後代、子嗣', 'Offspring', '/ˈɔːfˌsprɪŋ/', 'Parents invest considerable resources in their offspring''s education.', '父母在其後代的教育上投入相當多的資源。', '3', 20),
('過度保護的', 'Overprotective', '/ˌoʊvərprəˈtektɪv/', 'Overprotective parents may hinder their children''s independence.', '過度保護的父母可能阻礙孩子的獨立性。', '3', 20),
('父權家庭', 'Patriarchal family', '/ˌpeɪtriˈɑːrkəl ˈfæməli/', 'Traditional patriarchal families are led by the eldest male.', '傳統的父權家庭由年長男性領導。', '3', 20);
INSERT INTO vocabularies (chinese, english, phonetic, example_en, example_cn, grade, category_id) VALUES
('寬容的、放任的', 'Permissive', '/pərˈmɪsɪv/', 'Permissive parenting styles allow children more freedom to make decisions.', '寬容的教養方式讓孩子有更多自由做決定。', '3', 20),
('進步的', 'Progressive', '/prəˈɡresɪv/', 'Progressive families embrace gender equality in household duties.', '進步的家庭在家務分工上擁抱性別平等。', '3', 20),
('保護性的', 'Protective', '/prəˈtektɪv/', 'Asian parents are often described as being protective of their children''s future.', '亞洲父母經常被描述為對子女的未來具有保護性。', '3', 20),
('兄弟姊妹', 'Siblings', '/ˈsɪblɪŋz/', 'Research shows that children with siblings tend to develop better social skills.', '研究顯示有兄弟姊妹的孩子往往發展出更好的社交技能。', '3', 20),
('獨生子女家庭', 'Single-child family', '/ˈsɪŋɡəl tʃaɪld ˈfæməli/', 'Single-child families are increasingly common in urban areas.', '獨生子女家庭在城市地區越來越常見。', '3', 20),
('單親家庭', 'Single-parent household', '/ˈsɪŋɡəl ˈperənt ˈhaʊshoʊld/', 'Single-parent households face unique challenges in balancing work and childcare.', '單親家庭在平衡工作和育兒方面面臨獨特挑戰。', '3', 20),
('姊妹', 'Sister', '/ˈsɪstər/', 'My sister is my closest confidant.', '我的姊妹是我最親密的知己。', '3', 20),
('嫂子/弟媳/姊夫的姊妹', 'Sister-in-law', '/ˈsɪstər ɪn lɔː/', 'My sister-in-law is also my best friend.', '我的嫂子也是我最好的朋友。', '3', 20),
('兒子', 'Son', '/sʌn/', 'Their eldest son is currently studying abroad in Canada.', '他們的長子目前在加拿大留學。', '3', 20),
('女婿', 'Son-in-law', '/sʌn ɪn lɔː/', 'Their son-in-law is a respected doctor.&nbsp;', '他們的女婿是一位受人尊敬的醫生。', '3', 20),
('配偶', 'Spouse', '/spaʊs/', 'Modern couples often discuss career priorities with their spouse before making major decisions.', '現代夫妻在做重大決定前經常與配偶討論職業優先順序。', '3', 20),
('繼兄弟', 'Stepbrother', '/ˈstepˌbrʌðər/', 'My stepbrother and I get along very well.', '我的繼兄弟和我相處得很好。', '3', 20),
('繼父', 'Stepfather', '/ˈstepˌfɑːðər/', 'My stepfather married my mother when I was ten.', '我的繼父在我十歲時與我母親結婚。', '3', 20),
('繼母', 'Stepmother', '/ˈstepˌmʌðər/', 'My stepmother has been very kind and supportive.', '我的繼母一直很善良且支持我。', '3', 20),
('繼父母', 'Stepparent', '/ˈstepˌperənt/', 'Having a stepparent can provide additional support.', '有繼父母可以提供額外的支持。', '3', 20),
('繼兄弟姊妹', 'Stepsibling', '/ˈstepˌsɪblɪŋ/', 'My stepsiblings and I share holiday traditions.', '我的繼兄弟姊妹和我分享節日傳統。', '3', 20),
('繼姊妹', 'Stepsister', '/ˈstepˌsɪstər/', 'My stepsister introduced me to her circle of friends.', '我的繼姊妹把我介紹給她的朋友圈。', '3', 20),
('支持的', 'Supportive', '/səˈpɔːrtɪv/', 'Having supportive family members significantly impacts one''s mental health.', '擁有支持性的家庭成員對心理健康有重大影響。', '3', 20),
('傳統的', 'Traditional', '/trəˈdɪʃənəl/', 'Traditional families often emphasize respect for elders.', '傳統的家庭通常強調尊敬長輩。', '3', 20),
('叔叔/伯伯/舅舅', 'Uncle', '/ˈʌŋkəl/', 'My uncle tells the best stories at family dinners.', '我的叔叔在家庭聚餐時說最好聽的故事。', '3', 20),
('教養、成長環境', 'Upbringing', '/ˈʌpˌbrɪŋɪŋ/', 'My upbringing in a multicultural family shaped my worldview.', '我在多元文化家庭的教養塑造了我的世界觀。', '3', 20),
('妻子', 'Wife', '/waɪf/', 'His wife is a successful entrepreneur.', '他的妻子是一位成功的企業家。', '3', 20),
('關於', 'about', '/ə''baʊt/', 'Tell me about your dog.', '告訴我關於你狗狗的事。', '3', 21),
('在…以後 aunt', 'after', '/''æftɚ/', 'I go home after school.', '我放學後回家。', '3', 21),
('再一次', 'again', '/ə''ɡɛn/', 'Please say it again.', '請再說一次。', '3', 21),
('同意', 'agree', '/ə''ɡri/', 'I agree with you.', '我同意你的看法。', '3', 21),
('總是', 'always', '/''ɔlwez/', 'I always eat breakfast.', '我總是吃早餐。', '3', 21),
('動物', 'animal', '/''ænəməl/', 'The cat is a cute animal.', '貓是一隻可愛的動物。', '3', 21),
('秋天', 'autumn', '/''ɔtəm/', 'Leaves fall in autumn.', '秋天時葉子掉落。', '3', 21),
('香蕉', 'banana', '/bə''nænə/', 'I like to eat banana.', '我喜歡吃香蕉。', '3', 21),
('棒球', 'baseball', '/''besbɔl/', 'He plays baseball.', '他打棒球。', '3', 21),
('籃子', 'basket', '/''bæskɪt/', 'Put the apple in the basket.', '把蘋果放在籃子裡。', '3', 21),
